description:
&lt;p&gt;We have full and part-time Healthcare Assistant opportunities across Buckinghamshire Healthcare NHS Trust. Our main sites include Stoke Mandeville, High Wycombe and Amersham Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These are great opportunities for candidates who are looking to step into healthcare for the first time, or for those who are already in healthcare and want to work for an NHS Trust. The role is based in both acute and rehab areas, and across our teams which include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General medicine wards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Surgical and critical care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;National Spinal Injuries Centre&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paediatrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not only will you be joining a team of dedicated professionals who you will learn from on the job, the Trust will provide development and training to ensure you have the skills for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If your application is shortlisted successfully you will receive an invitation and further information regarding the assessments. You will sit a 40 minute English and Math assessment, if successful you will be taken through to the interview stage. Please note you will not be required to sit the test if you can provide certificate evidence of GSCE level C and above in Maths and English (current grade 4 and above).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note, most of our wards work a 24 hour shift rotation across a 7 day service (with the exception of Outpatient areas and Theatres). Day shifts typically start at 7/7.30am – 7/7.30pm and night shifts are vice versa.The minimum part time hours we recruit to is 24 hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gary Kurtis, Recruitment Attractions Officer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address : gary.kurtis@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number : 07816 856555&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;bht.hcarecruitment@nhs.net or 01494 734868&lt;/p&gt;
